 mix <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix a further <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a bowl."},{"content":"Shape 35 meatballs (approx. 1 oz ea.) and place 1 inch apart on prepared baking sheet. Bake for 25 minutes (350°F). Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and make BBQ sauce."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Strawberry BBQ Sauce"},{"content":"Place onion and garlic into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add strawberries, ketchup, water, brown sugar, mustard, paprika, vinegar, Worcestershire, salt and pepper and mix <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Place simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid and cook <b>15 min\/212°F\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add chipotle chili, insert measuring cup and blend <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b><b>-7<b>, increasing speed gradually."},{"content":"Transfer meatballs to a serving bowl and cover in Strawberry BBQ Sauce. Garnish with chopped parsley and serve hot."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For a main dish, serve hot over steamed rice."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","45m","35 pieces"]}